The article announces several nominations and appointments made on September 4, 2020. Here are the key points:

1. Matthew B. Shipley from Virginia has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Defense (Readiness). He currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Force Readiness. Shipley has extensive experience in military and strategic planning.

2. Ryan Michael Tully from New York has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of State (Verification and Compliance). He currently holds a senior position in the National Security Council and has previously worked in the Senate and the Office of the Assistant Secretary of the Navy.

3. Rear Admiral (Ret.) Jon C. Kreitz from Virginia has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Air Force (Manpower and Reserve Affairs). He has held various leadership positions in the Department of the Navy and has extensive experience in operations and personnel management.

